ut\",\"category\":\"code_quality\",\"title\":\"Audit credential deletion and access operations\",\"description\":\"Only credential creation (key:encrypt) produces an audit log entry in httpApi.ts. Credential deletion (DELETE /api/credentials/:id) and credential listing for a persona (GET /api/personas/:id/credentials) leave no audit trail. Add auditLog.record() calls for key:delete and key:access actions at those endpoints, including the tenantId and resourceId. This closes a compliance-critical gap in the credential lifecycle.\",\"reasoning\":\"For any system handling encrypted secrets, the full credential lifecycle must be auditable. An attacker or rogue admin could delete credentials to cover tracks, and the current code would leave zero evidence. The audit infrastructure already exists; the gap is just missing call sites at deletion and access endpoints.\",\"status\":\"pending\",\"user_feedback\":null,\"user_pattern\":0,\"effort\":2,\"impact\":9,\"implemented_at\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026-03-18T11:53:50.160Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-18T11:53:50.160Z\",\"requirement_id\":null,\"goal_id\":null,\"risk\":2,\"provider\":null,\"model\":null,\"detailed\":0}}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
[2026-03-18T11:53:50.757Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PZgyPWnsf1GEqYRHsYhqNK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01PZxgp9MguMgByiwZUmZxut","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"scan_id\": \"0e5ab481-52cf-45a9-aeb0-f04397a63a1b\",\n    \"project_id\": \"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\",\n    \"scan_type\": \"observability_scout\",\n    \"category\": \"code_quality\",\n    \"title\": \"Add error handling to maintainCache() timer\",\n    \"description\": \"TenantKeyManager.maintainCache() runs on a 60-second interval and awaits Promise.all() for key derivations, but has no try/catch. If any derivation throws, the rejected promise is unobserved — Node.js emits unhandledRejection and the maintenance cycle silently stops working. Wrap the method body in try/catch, log the error with context (which tenantId failed, how many succeeded), and ensure the timer continues for the next cycle.\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"Silent maintenance timer failures are insidious — the cache appears to work but keys gradually expire without renewal, eventually causing a burst of synchronous derivations under load. This is exactly the kind of failure that surfaces as a mysterious latency spike during peak traffic. A simple try/catch with structured logging prevents this entire failure mode.\",\n    \"effort\": 1,\n    \"impact\": 7,\n    \"risk\": 1\n  }'","description":"Save idea 4"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1000,"cache_read_input_tokens":45630,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1000},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6b375ece-41c0-48fe-9151-de360e723e96","uuid":"fe79b66b-a317-439b-a397-dce75aa522cb"}
